        <p>Now that you understand Models (data structure) and Views (data display), let's explore how to <strong>store data permanently</strong> using databases. In the .NET world, we primarily use <strong>Entity Framework Core</strong> (EF Core) to work with databases.</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> <strong>Good news for beginners:</strong> Entity Framework does most of the hard work for you! You work with C# objects, and EF Core automatically translates them to database operations.
